    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Chamonix</placeName>
                    <date>July 10. 1881</date>
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>It is extremely kind of you to suggest sending your spare copy of my book to Fritz Müller &amp; I enclose a slip of paper with ‘From the author’ written on it; though I feel that under the circumstances the book ought to be rather regarded as your gift than as mine.</p>
<p>In any case there is nobody to whom it would please me more to have the copy sent than to Fritz Müller.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I thank you most heartily for your kind congratulations on the completion of the work, &amp; I only trust that it may prove worthy of the praise you have bestowed on it.</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | F. M. Balfour</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD had suggested giving his spare copy of Balfour’s <hi rend="italic">A treatise on comparative embryology</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_337.xml">Balfour 1880–1</ref>) to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3070.xml">Müller</ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13235.xml">letter to F. M. Balfour, 6 July 1881</ref>).</note>
        </div>
    
